42858525ad2\r\n\t{\n\nmargin-right:0in;\nmargin-bottom:7.5pt;\nmargin-left:0in;\nfont-size:12.0pt;\nfont-family:\"Times New Roman\", \"serif\";}\n#ygrps-yiv-1342858525 p.ygrps-yiv-1342858525underline1, #ygrps-yiv-1342858525 li.ygrps-yiv-1342858525underline1, #ygrps-yiv-1342858525 div.ygrps-yiv-1342858525underline1\r\n\t{\n\nmargin-right:0in;\n\nmargin-left:0in;\nfont-size:12.0pt;\nfont-family:\"Times New Roman\", \"serif\";\ntext-decoration:underline;}\n#ygrps-yiv-1342858525 span.ygrps-yiv-1342858525yshortcuts1\r\n\t{\nfont-family:\"Verdana\", \"sans-serif\";\nfont-weight:bold;}\n#ygrps-yiv-1342858525 span.ygrps-yiv-1342858525yshortcuts2\r\n\t{\nfont-family:\"Verdana\", \"sans-serif\";\nfont-weight:normal;}\n#ygrps-yiv-1342858525 span.ygrps-yiv-1342858525EmailStyle35\r\n\t{\nfont-family:Inconsolata;\ncolor:#1F497D;}\n#ygrps-yiv-1342858525 .ygrps-yiv-1342858525MsoChpDefault\r\n\t{\nfont-size:10.0pt;}\n _filtered #ygrps-yiv-1342858525 {\nmargin:1.0in 1.0in 1.0in 1.0in;}\n#ygrps-yiv-1342858525 div.ygrps-yiv-1342858525WordSection1\r\n\t{}\n#ygrps-yiv-1342858525  \n _filtered #ygrps-yiv-1342858525 {\n}\n _filtered #ygrps-yiv-1342858525 {\n\n\n\n\n\nfont-family:Symbol;}\n _filtered #ygrps-yiv-1342858525 {\n\n\n\n\n\nfont-family:\"Courier New\";\n}\n _filtered #ygrps-yiv-1342858525 {\n\n\n\n\n\nfont-family:Wingdings;}\n _filtered #ygrps-yiv-1342858525 {\n\n\n\n\n\nfont-family:Wingdings;}\n _filtered #ygrps-yiv-1342858525 {\n\n\n\n\n\nfont-family:Wingdings;}\n _filtered #ygrps-yiv-1342858525 {\n\n\n\n\n\nfont-family:Wingdings;}\n _filtered #ygrps-yiv-1342858525 {\n\n\n\n\n\nfont-family:Wingdings;}\n _filtered #ygrps-yiv-1342858525 {\n\n\n\n\n\nfont-family:Wingdings;}\n _filtered #ygrps-yiv-1342858525 {\n\n\n\n\n\nfont-family:Wingdings;}\n#ygrps-yiv-1342858525 ol\r\n\t{margin-bottom:0in;}\n#ygrps-yiv-1342858525 ul\r\n\t{margin-bottom:0in;}\n--></style>\r\n</head>\r\n \r\n<div class=\"ygrps-yiv-1342858525WordSection1\">\r\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-1342858525MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Inconsolata;color:#1F497D;\">This is exactly what continuous integration servers like Bamboo and Jenkins provide.&nbsp; It’s not effective to try to duplicate that functionality at the JUnit level.</span></p> \r\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-1342858525MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Inconsolata;color:#1F497D;\"> &nbsp;</span></p> \r\n<div style=\"border:none;border-left:solid blue 1.5pt;padding:0in 0in 0in 4.0pt;\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div style=\"border:none;border-top:solid #B5C4DF 1.0pt;padding:3.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\">\r\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-1342858525MsoNormal\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">From:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\"> junit@yahoogroups.com [mailto:junit@yahoogroups.com]\r\n<br>\r\n<b>Sent:</b> Saturday, June 07, 2014 10:08 AM<br>\r\n<b>To:</b> junit@yahoogroups.com<br>\r\n<b>Subject:</b> [junit] Tool to detect who broke a particular test</span></p> \r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-1342858525MsoNormal\"> &nbsp;</p> \r\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-1342858525MsoNormal\">&nbsp; </p> \r\n<div id=\"ygrps-yiv-1342858525ygrp-mlmsg\">\r\n<div id=\"ygrps-yiv-1342858525ygrp-msg\">\r\n<div id=\"ygrps-yiv-1342858525ygrp-text\">\r\n<p>Hi@all<br>\r\n<br>\r\ni&#39;d like to discuss an idea i had for a legacy project i was working for. We had the problem that a large number of developers were working on the same code base, and the unit tests ran only once a night as a nightly build with a huge load of unit tests and\r\n a large set of integration tests.<br>\r\n<br>\r\nEvery night a number of tests broke. And due to the large number of commits during the day it was hard to detect who broke which test. I know that the problem here is the test and project setup and module size, but due to other limitations we were not able\r\n to change this in a useful amount of time.<br>\r\n<br>\r\nSo, i sat down and wrote a small library to fill the missing gap. Basically it is a simple Java VM agent. The agent instruments the loaded classes and unit tests and adds logging capability to every affected class. For every successful test it creates a log\r\n per test method with the affected classes. For every negative test, it just logs which class changed since the last positive result. It connects with the VCS(Git, SVN) to get the latest revision and author for a given Java class, so it is easy to find who\r\n broke a test.<br>\r\n<br>\r\nThe project is still in an early stage, but working. The sources are available here:<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://github.com/mirkosertic/WhoBrokeIt\">mirkosertic/WhoBrokeIt</a></p> \r\n<div id=\"ygrps-yiv-1342858525enhancrCard_1\">\r\n<table class=\"ygrps-yiv-1342858525MsoNormalTable\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" width=\"450\" style=\"width:337.5pt;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height:.75pt;\">\r\n<td colspan=\"6\" style=\"background:#E5E5E5;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;height:.75pt;\"></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"1\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:.75pt;background:#E5E5E5;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;\">\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"168\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:1.75in;background:black;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;\">\r\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-1342858525MsoNormal\" align=\"center\" style=\"text-align:center;\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://github.com/mirkosertic/WhoBrokeIt\"><span style=\"color:black;text-decoration:none;\"><img border=\"0\" width=\"168\" height=\"168\" id=\"ygrps-yiv-1342858525_x0000_i1025\" src=\"https://ec.yimg.com/ec?url=https%3A%2F%2Favatars2.githubusercontent.com%2Fu%2F2124663%3Fs%3D400&t=1572967053&sig=ATKxe34cilNirIIg0oVxgg--~E\" alt=\"image\"></span></a></p> \r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"1\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:.75pt;background:#E5E5E5;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;\">\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"100%\" colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:100.0%;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-1342858525MsoNormal\" style=\"background:white;\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://github.com/mirkosertic/WhoBrokeIt\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-1342858525link-enhancr-element\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;color:black;text-decoration:none;\">mirkosertic/WhoBrokeIt</span></span><span style=\"color:black;text-decoration:none;\">\r\n</span></a></p> \r\n<div>\r\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-1342858525MsoNormal\" style=\"background:white;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;color:#999999;\">WhoBrokeIt is a simple library to detect which VCS commit broke a particular unit test.</span></p> \r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"1\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:.75pt;background:#E5E5E5;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;\">\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;\">\r\n<div>\r\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-1342858525MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:1.0pt;\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://github.com/mirkosertic/WhoBrokeIt\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-1342858525link-enhancr-element\"><span style=\"font-size:7.0pt;color:#999999;text-decoration:none;\">View on\r\n<b>github.com</b> </span></span></a></span></p> \r\n</div>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"100\" style=\"width:75.0pt;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;\">\r\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-1342858525MsoNormal\" align=\"right\" style=\"text-align:right;\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-1342858525link-enhancr-element\"><span style=\"font-size:7.0pt;color:#999999;\">Preview by Yahoo\r\n</span></span><span style=\"font-size:1.0pt;\"></span></p> \r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height:.75pt;\">\r\n<td colspan=\"6\" style=\"background:#E5E5E5;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;height:.75pt;\"></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr height=\"0\">\r\n<td width=\"0\" style=\"border:none;\"></td>\r\n<td width=\"168\" style=\"border:none;\"></td>\r\n<td width=\"0\" style=\"border:none;\"></td>\r\n<td width=\"125\" style=\"border:none;\"></td>\r\n<td width=\"156\" style=\"border:none;\"></td>\r\n<td width=\"0\" style=\"border:none;\"></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p> \r\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-1342858525MsoNormal\"><br>\r\n<br>\r\nThe next features I would like to implement are multi-module builds and CI system integration. But first of all i would like to hear opinions about this tool, and of course if anybody is interested to contribute, he or she is very welcome!<br>\r\n<br>\r\nKind regards,<br>\r\nMirko</p> \r\n<p> &nbsp;</p> \r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-1342858525MsoNormal\"><span style=\"color:white;\"></span></p> \r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n \r\n</div></div></html></div>", 
